<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-10T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/312: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-10T14:00:00-05:00">September 10, 1934—2
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>98. My telegram No. 97 September 7, 1 p.m. President Vincent has decided
                            not to send Blanchet an amended text for consideration at Wednesday
                            meeting owing to inability to obtain assurances from Senators as to
                            desired modifications.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Woodward</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>